{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Handle null task for 'property' type in createTask",
    "body": "This commit fixes an issue where a null task was returned when creating a task of type 'property' in the createTask method. A quick fix is implemented to add the task definition for 'property' and recreate the task if it is null. This ensures that the task is properly initialized and returned."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Fix resource map loading order in Translate task",
    "body": "This commit fixes the order in which resource maps are loaded in the Translate task. Previously, the order was incorrect, which could lead to incorrect resource usage. The fix ensures that the most specific resource is used by processing bundle files in a specific order. This change affects the loadResourceMaps method, which now loads resource maps for the specified locale and default locale in the correct order."
}

{
    "type": "refactor",
    "subject": "Change finalize method access modifier to protected",
    "body": "This commit changes the access modifier of the finalize method from public to protected. Additionally, it adds a call to super.finalize() to ensure proper cleanup. This refactoring improves the internal structure of the CBZip2OutputStream class, making it more maintainable and easier to understand."
}

{
    "type": "style",
    "subject": "Add missing import statement",
    "body": "Added the necessary import statement for ByteArrayInputStream in TarRoundTripTest.java to ensure proper functionality."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Correctly categorize symbolic links in FTP directory scan",
    "body": "Fixed an issue in the scandir method where symbolic links were incorrectly added to dirsExcluded instead of filesExcluded. This change ensures that symbolic links are properly categorized during FTP directory scans."
}

{
    "type": "style",
    "subject": "Update Javadoc comment to use English",
    "body": "Replace German phrase 'fuer' with English 'for' in Javadoc comment of StyleTest.java to improve readability and consistency."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Improve SQL execution result handling",
    "body": "Fixed the logic for handling SQL execution results in the execSQL method. Previously, the method checked for non-null result sets or non-negative update counts to determine when to stop processing results. This commit changes the logic to rely on the return value of getMoreResults, which is a more reliable indicator of whether there are more results to process. This change ensures that all results are properly handled and logged."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Handle null values when declaring beans in ScriptRunner",
    "body": "This commit fixes an issue where null values were being passed to the declareBean method in ScriptRunner. Now, if a null value is encountered, the corresponding bean is undeclared to prevent it from being visible. This change ensures that the ScriptRunner correctly handles null values when executing scripts with the Bean Scripting Framework (BSF)."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Update log level from debug to verbose in targetStarted method",
    "body": "Changed the log level from Project.MSG_DEBUG to Project.MSG_VERBOSE in the targetStarted method of CommonsLoggingListener class. This modification provides more detailed feedback to the user about the build process. The method now logs a verbose message when a target starts execution, instead of a debug message."
}

{
